text: Kazenambo Kazenambo (6 July 1963 â€“ 17 August 2021) was a Botswanan-born Namibian politician. He was a member of SWAPO. In 2004, he was elected to the National Assembly. He retired in 2014. Kazenambo was born in Maun, Botswana. Kazenambo died in Windhoek, Namibia on 17 August 2021 from COVID-19 problems, aged 58. ==References== Category:1963 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Namibia Category:Botswana politicians Category:SWAPO politicians
